column1: Will Gotabaya Rajapaksa cease to be the president of Sri Lanka before 20 July 2022?
column6: ['Society', 'Economic Policy', 'Leader Entry/Exit', 'Non-US Politics']
President Gotabaya Rajapaksa resigns after arriving in Singapore

Handing over business to his friend & crony PM, Rajapaksa apparently tries to skip resigning expressis verbis; his current stay is in the Maledives, "from where he issued a gazette stating that he is 'unable to exercise, perform and discharge the powers, duties and functions of the Office of the President' by reason of his absence from Sri Lanka". It appears he continues to consider himself a president in exile and supposingly intends to pick up duties again as soon as he hits land.
https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/jul/14/sri-lanka-on-a-knife-edge-as-promised-rajapaksa-resignation-fails-to-arrive

According to popular news reports, President Rajapasksa is due to resign after the resignation of the Prime Minister and the storming of his residence by protestors (https://www.cbsnews.com/news/sri-lankans-storm-presidents-house-office-in-biggest-rally/).
https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/sri-lanka-police-fire-tear-gas-anti-government-protesters-2022-07-09/
"Mr Rajapaksa will step down on 13 July. PM Wickremesinghe has agreed to resign."
verified video of the President running as fast as he can up the gangway to a Military Ship. Have not confirmed his destination.

“There was no direct confirmation about the potential resignation from Mr. Rajapaksa, who is in hiding and who in the past has remained defiant. Mr. Abeywardena, in a televised statement, said the president had informed him he would resign on July 13, “to ensure a peaceful transition of power.” “
https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2022/7/9/sri-lanka-protesters-storm-president-house-demanding-resignation
Updated per storming of PM palace and request of President's resignation.
Rioters ran him out of the palace this morning and he is said to be in hiding.
https://www.nytimes.com/live/2022/07/09/world/sri-lanka-protests-rajapaksa

Passage of time + short time remaining until Question resolves + no specific reported “in flight” developments that might suddenly change the picture within the next few days. (Chance of yes now assessed at < 0.5%)
- Average duration for a President of Sri Lanka is about 7 years (GR is just 2.5 years in)
only if his step sister admits to being a clandestine intelligence officer for a unarmed country and spy organization

- https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-06-06/sri-lanka-leader-vows-to-finish-term-won-t-run-for-re-election Rajapaksa has stated that he will finish his term (but plans to not run for reelection)

- The president and prime ministers were brothers. The prime minister recently resigned on May 9 after the economic crisis https://www.npr.org/2022/05/09/1097562723/the-prime-minister-of-sri-lanka-resigns-after-weeks-of-protests

vor allem vor dem Hintergrund der andauernden Proteste und des Symbols, das Rajapaksa verkörpert, nämlich von Korruption und Vetternwirtschaft, denke ich, dass die Eliten des Landes den Rücktritt des Präsidenten fordern, um weitere Ausschreitungen zu verhindern.
